President Obama met with African Union Chairperson Dr. Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma in South Africa to congratulate her on the 50th anniversary of the formation of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) /African Union. They discussed the U.S.-African Union partnership, regional peace and security efforts, and the African Union's role in advancing development and democratic norms. They also talked about empowering women and youth, expanding trade and investment, and creating broad-based prosperity in Africa.